note._content: Belfast Castle is still there.  Now owned by the City Council it is one of NI's most popular wedding venues.  We were one of the couples that have been married there.
note.author: 24366212@N07

note._content: All of this land has since been developed into housing as Belfast as grown.
note.author: 24366212@N07

note._content: This rocky outcrop near the summit of the Cave Hill is known as Napoleon's Nose
note.author: 10135259@N04

note._content: also mac art's fort, where some of the high kings or ireland were crowned
note.author: 13227773@N08

note._content: this is the right angle to see why that outcrop is called napoleon's nose.  it is supposed to look like his whole head in fact, mouth and lips to the right, forehead to the left.  it inspired the story of the giant in gulliver's travels by jonathan swift
note.author: 13227773@N08
